text: I read this intro and put some notes here: <https://hyp.is/go?url=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.treenotation.org%2Fliber-simplicitas.html&group=__world__>

Hey! It’s Matt Keeter! I was thinking this was similar to Antimony and lo and behold, this is a successor. I had studied your codebase for kokopelli and wrote a toy diffing algorithm in javascript based on your work there. How come kokopelli and antimony were abandoned, and you keep starting over on new projects? Did you discover a deadend with each of those?
